# Cloud: AWS

## Service Selection
| Need | AWS Service | Notes |
|------|-------------|-------|
| Compute (containers) | ECS Fargate / EKS | Fargate for simplicity, EKS for Kubernetes |
| Compute (functions) | Lambda | <15 min execution, <10 GB memory |
| API Gateway | API Gateway / ALB | API GW for serverless, ALB for containers |
| Database (relational) | RDS / Aurora | Aurora for high availability |
| Database (NoSQL) | DynamoDB | Single-digit ms latency at any scale |
| Cache | ElastiCache (Redis) | Session store, query cache |
| Queue | SQS / EventBridge | SQS for point-to-point, EventBridge for fan-out |
| Storage | S3 | Use lifecycle rules for cost optimization |
| Secrets | Secrets Manager / SSM Parameter Store | Secrets Manager for rotation |

## Security
- Use IAM roles for service-to-service auth; **never** access keys in code
- Apply least-privilege IAM policies; scope to specific resources with ARNs
- Enable CloudTrail in all accounts and regions
- Use VPC endpoints for S3, DynamoDB, and other supported services
- Enable GuardDuty for threat detection
- Use `[AWS_ACCOUNT_ID]` placeholder in docs — never real account IDs

## Networking
- Use private subnets for compute and database resources
- Public subnets only for load balancers and NAT gateways
- Use Security Groups as the primary network firewall
- Enable VPC Flow Logs for network monitoring

## Cost
- Tag all resources: `project`, `environment`, `owner`, `cost-center`
- Use Savings Plans or Reserved Instances for predictable workloads
- Use Spot Instances for fault-tolerant batch workloads
- Set up AWS Budgets with alerts at 80% and 100% thresholds
- Review Cost Explorer monthly; right-size underutilized instances

## Conventions
- Use IaC (Terraform, CDK, or CloudFormation) for all resources
- Resource naming: `{project}-{env}-{service}-{qualifier}`
- One AWS account per environment (dev, staging, prod) via AWS Organizations
- Enable default encryption on S3 buckets, EBS volumes, and RDS instances
